@startuml
title Viaverse Auth / Authorization / Rate Limit — Activity Diagram
start
:API request;
:TLS + WAF / edge checks;
:Rate limit\nIP/device/account;
:Validate token\nsignature/expiry/audience;
if (Valid token?) then (yes)
  :Load claims/capabilities;
  :Evaluate RBAC/ABAC\nownership + capability;
  if (Allowed?) then (yes)
    :Create security context\ncorrelationId;
    :Execute use case;
    :Audit if sensitive;
    :Return response\nredacted fields only;
  else (no)
    :Reject 403\nno data leak;
  endif
else (no)
  :Reject 401/429\nsafe error;
endif
stop

note bottom
Never trust only UI state.
Every backend use case checks capability, ownership,
resource state and policy before changing data.
end note
@enduml
